  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Helicobacter pylori is strongly associated to the development of gastrointestinal disorders.
      Emerging antibiotic resistance and poor patient compliance of modern therapies has resulted
      in significant eradication failure. Clinical trial was conducted to see the efficacy of
      current quadruple and phytomedicine-based therapies for the eradication of H. pylori
      infection and relief in its associated symptoms in Pakistan.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
